FT  10 NOV 94 / International Company News: Sales to SA telecoms help lift
Reunert 18%
Reunert, the South African technology group, has posted an 18 per cent
increase in pre-tax profit to R304m (Dollars 87m) for the year to September
from R257.9m, helped by increased sales to South African parastatals Eskom
and Telkom, writes Mark Suzman in Johannesburg. A final dividend of 19.5
cents has been declared, bringing the total for the year up 15 per cent to
27 cents compared with 23.4 cents.
